H.B. 539
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Mar 26, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10254-NIf-58C
Short Title: Revenue Neutral Rate Required. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Blust.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE UNITS OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT TO ADOPT A REVENUE
3 NEUTRAL TAX RATE IN THE YEAR OF A GENERAL REAPPRAISAL.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 159-13 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 159-13. The budget ordinance; form, adoption, limitations, tax levy, filing.
7 …
8 (c) The budget ordinance of a local government shall levy taxes on property at rates that
9 will produce the revenue necessary to balance appropriations and revenues, after taking into
10 account the estimated percentage of the levy that will not be collected during the fiscal year. The
11 budget ordinance of a public authority shall be balanced so that appropriations do not exceed
12 revenues.
13 (c1) For every year in which a general reappraisal of real property has been conducted in
14 a local government, the budget ordinance of that local government shall levy taxes on property
15 for that year at the revenue-neutral tax rate set out in G.S. 159-11(e).
16 …."
17 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to budget
18 ordinances passed on or after that date.
*DRH10254-NIf-58C*

